greeting = "To My Kin in Moss,"
signoff = "By Her Grace,

Briallon
(Chieftess of the Mosswyn Fungal Clan)"
summerVersion = "Tender greetings, my friend! My name is Chieftess Briallon Sporebloom, although I go by many names—Herald Sporebloom, Rootspeaker, The Great Mycelian (which I personally feel is a touch zealous)—but you may simply call me Briallon. 

Contrary to common gossip, I am a simple woman. I lead a humble people, I preach an honest doctrine, and I have but one desire: to advocate for the natural world, as only She can save us. Please do not think me harsh when I say this, for I love our neighbors as I love all brethren of Moss, but…what do the Dwarves know of nurturing the soil? What do the Bonefolk know of the sanctity of death, or the Skyfolk of the music of rot? Nothing! And that is where we must come in.

This Dry season, Moss has brought upon us a glorious opportunity to encounter one another in the midst of diplomacy and in the heat of passion. Mosswyn’s glorious forest scape, teeming with boundless fresh vegetation, has much to offer you humans. As plague threatens your sacred land, Moss desires only to expand and help her sons and daughters guard the sanctity of nature. As lack of faith in Her grace and power wilts, I am deeply ashamed to admit that we are currently disappointing Her in this respect. She may demand drastic measures for us to regain the validity and purity we desperately need. In the meantime, all I ask is that you consider me with sincerity, and I hope to hear from you soon."
