springVersion = "The time is upon us! You have sensibly elected to remain in contact. I thank Moss for granting you wisdom!

Speaking of wisdom—one of my clergyfae have informed me of recent correspondence entering your kingdom from Mosswyn (my network of informants is invaluable in keeping me updated on all of the goings-on in the northern continent)! That being said, I’d like to confirm: is it true that Priestess Hindhart has reached out to you? 

I only ask because I know her well. Very well. It’s embarrassing, but we were actually lovers, once. We didn’t end on the best terms, which is why I know that she may attempt to slander my name and good character. Do not believe her lies. She could never understand the depth of my faith—quite unfortunate for the daughter of a High Priestess. 

Not that I can completely blame her; it takes a special capacity to grasp the enormity of Moss’s love, and the great measures that She demands from us in turn. And yet, I am determined to spread Her teachings throughout our kingdoms, so that all may know Her glory and judgment! Really—is that so much to ask?"
